summary:
I am a natural leader, and have abundant experience as master diver. However, I have also fulfilled many other roles, and am very much a team player. Moreover, I have a wide and varied skill set, which includes the construction, maintenance and surveillance of pipe lines, sewer systems, marinas, bridges and much more. Additionally, I have a great deal of knowledge of and experience in construction, and have used these for effective on-the-spot trouble shooting. I am used to spend significant amounts of time on diving sites, both in and off shore. I received extensive training and have copious work experience in handling welding equipment (Master 2850, Millers RHC-14, Arcair Seatorch, Oxy/Act Torch,BROCO) and hydraulic/ pneumatic tools (hammers, drills, sews, wrenches, Manta Ray Bar Drive Steel Extractor, as well as bolt guns, brash carts, power jet wash brushes, hydraulic jack lifts, pneumatic lift mats, air/water suction pumps, lift bags). Naturally, I also regularly used a wide variety of hand tools in both my training and work dives.

Dutch Cat A Certification. 
Dutch Cat B Certification
Safety for Operational Supervisors VCA-VOL
HSE Part 1 Wet Bell Diver.
HSE Part 3 Surface Supplied Diver.
Seaman's book
Croatian Cat A Certification. 
Croatian Cat B Certification
Professional SCUBA Diver.
HSE First Aid at Work.
OPITO BOSEIT Offshore Survival (HUET & EBA)
OPITO Minimum Industry Safety Training.
Cutting & Burning Accredited (Broco).
Hydraulic Tools Accredited
Pneumatic Tools Accredited
